$interpreted: Haunted House Assistant: Boss... Are we really gonna go through with this?
Haunted House Assistant: We're already raking in the dough with our annual Ritual Special, we needn't take such risks—
Haunted House Boss: What short-sighted cowardice. We'll never get rich and famous with that attitude.
Haunted House Assistant: But this book—this is real dark stuff...
Haunted House Boss: ...Once we've used the True Night's Ritual to catch ourselves a real ghost, our haunted house will become a sensation! People will flock from all around to test their courage...
Haunted House Boss: And not just for our fantastic promotions!
Tindoiimu: ………
Toyokuni: ………
Toyokuni: ...This is your first time participating in the True Night's Ritual. If there's anything you're not sure of, just tell me.
Tindoiimu: Everything is in order. Thank you, Toyokuni.
Toyokuni: And if you've any concerns about the ceremony, you need only ask.
Tindoiimu: I haven't. It's all splendid.
Toyokuni: And about the stalls and vendors...
Tindoiimu: ...You really needn't worry about me. I'm here to represent the Insect Tribe, and I've done my homework accordingly.
Toyokuni: Well, it was my idea to have you join the grand ceremony this year. It's my responsibility to make sure you feel totally comfortable.
Tindoiimu: And why's that?
Toyokuni: The True Night's Ritual isn't just the Fog Sect's most supreme rite. It's a once-in-a-year opportunity for the dead to return to the world of the living.
Toyokuni: Their descendents greet them with banquets and celebrations so that they can find their way home again, to be reunited once more.
Tindoiimu: Reunited? But this is an Alliance tradition, so I don't see where the Insect Tribe come into it...
Toyokuni: For a long time now, the tribes of the East have sent representatives to partake of the ritual.
Toyokuni: But I believe that we shouldn't cling fast to the seperation of the Insect Tribe from our Alliance.
Tindoiimu: (...The Fog Sect must have enough enemies as it is. Why would they risk stirring up even more trouble with something like this...)
Toyokuni: Don't you pay any mind to those who'd oppose the Insects. In fact, there's more opposition to the attire this year than to your presence here.
Tindoiimu: The attire...
Tindoiimu: You mean these garments that everybody's wearing were provided by the Fog Sect?
Toyokuni: Yes. The season is especially muggy at this time of year, and so the Ancients developed and tailored this waterproof, fog-resistant material.
Toyokuni: This in turn inspired the merchants of the West, who further improved it into swimwear...
Toyokuni: This ritual will be the first to use this improved version imported directly from the West.
Tindoiimu: No wonder the style is so different from that in the East...
Tindoiimu: ………
Tindoiimu: (...Were there this many people here just a moment ago?)
Tindoiimu: (Strange, I'm suddenly feeling... so dizzy...)
Tindoiimu: —Gah!
Toyokuni: What is it?
Tindoiimu: ………
Tindoiimu: It's nothing, I just felt a little light-headed.
Toyokuni: ………
Toyokuni: When the living and the dead mingle together, those from outside the Fog Sect may be disturbed by malicious spirits.
Toyokuni: This protective Komainu Charm will keep you safe.
Tindoiimu: That's very kind, but—
Toyokuni: You can return it to me once the ritual is complete.
Toyokuni: ...It is finished.
Toyokuni: My tribe takes charge of patrols during this time, so I cannot be of further assistance. If you wish to understand more about the Fog Sect, you can ask for Lord Juan-Yun's help.
Tindoiimu: Juan-Yun?
Toyokuni: Haven't you heard? It appears that Juan-Yun plans to invite you to take a stroll with him.
Tindoiimu: ………
Tindoiimu: I don't feel well. I'll go back to the inn and rest. Excuse me.
Tindoiimu: Phew... I don't know what I'll do if Juan-Yun catches up with me.
Tindoiimu: The inn should be right up ahead now...
Haunted House Employee: I don't know nothin' about no inn~ But there's a haunted house right here!
Haunted House Employee: Where lost souls walk the night once again—Try yer luck at True Night's Haunted House!
Tindoiimu: Sorry, not interested.
Haunted House Employee: No interest? No problem! No guts is what you got to worry about.
Haunted House Employee: This ain't yer run o' the mill dress-up contest either. It's the real thing, in all it's heart-stoppin' terror!
Tindoiimu: (...Didn't he hear me the first time?)
Haunted House Employee: No problem if yer short on time, neither~
Haunted House Employee: We provide an express lane for our guests, so ye can get a taste of terror without no messin' around!
Tindoiimu: ………
Tindoiimu: (—What a salesman...)
Himawari: Juan-Yun! You clearly said you'd go with me alone to go get that Charm, so what do you wanna invite that troublesome girl along for!?
Juan-Yun: Hey~ It's the first time the Princess has joined a Fog Sect ceremony. Don't you think we should at least show her around a little?
Tindoiimu: (Oh no, I'll be in trouble if those two catch sight of me... Better find a hidding place—)
Haunted House Employee: Excuse me Miss, but you'll need to partner up with two companions before you can enter~
Tindoiimu: I'm short on time, just stick me with whoever—
Tipsy Contestant: ...What? Didn't you hear him?
Tipsy Contestant: I say, you need a partner, I need a partner, why don't we partner up and test our courage in there together~
Tipsy Contestant: Yaaagh, that hurts—
???: Master always warned me to use words before using force.
???: But Master also warned me that some people... won't listen if you don't make 'em.
Tipsy Contestant: You dare... you dare... strike me!? All right! Teaching spicy beauties like you a lesson is what I do best!!
???: Hah! Let's see you talk big when I'm through with you!
Tipsy Contestant: Owowowow, I was wrong! She's a tough talker—
Tipsy Contestant: You!! What's business of yours is this!?
Tindoiimu: None at all, but you're holding up the line.
Tipsy Contestant: Hmph!
Tipsy Contestant: Tsk tsk. That's a pretty face you've got. Where have I seen it before...
Tipsy Contestant: Ah! You wouldn't be—
Tindoiimu: —Where are the guards? Aren't they gonna come take out this trash?
Haunted House Guard: H-here! Apologies for any inconvenience!
???: Oh, it's my knight in shining armor... Just the kind of Eastern character I and my Master have been searching for.
???: If you're on your own, why don't you come partner up with us~
Tindoiimu: All right.
Miranda: I'm Miranda, by the way. I'm an exchange student from the Kingdom of the Sun.
Miranda: And yourself?
